note.p:
One of the three mental “poisons” (Skt. triviṣa) and one of six fundamental
                afflictions (Tib. rtsa nyon;
                  Skt. mūlakleśa).

One of the four attainments of the formless states. Also a
                class of devas in the formless realm (ārūpyadhātu). In this realm there is no body in this world, only mind;
                it is the result of accomplishing the formless meditative absorptions (ārūpyasamāpatti).

No Sanskrit sūtra with this title is known. The title may
                correspond with the name Kālaka or Kokālika, a partisan of Devadatta (see AN X.87);
                see Kudo 2004, p. 229, n. 2.
